annotation.TEXT: Okay, this time I'm serious!
Yep! And it also comes with a neat little box that shows which switch blocks are active.
Yep. (I think that explains why I couldn't get those coined munchers earlier when I hit the green P-switch-- because they weren't actually munchers to begin with!)
I might want to stop playing like an idiot for a moment...
Ow, that was dumb of me. Also, that red block is bouncy, but that particular white one doesn't seem to be doing anything...
Oh! I can kill them with a cape spin! Cool!
Let's try that again, shall we?
I wonder if I'll need to meet a coin quota at some point...
Ha! Knew it!
...What...
Okay, there's just one door left at the beginning, so let's see what it has to offer!
Oh, you're not fooling me again! Come on out, Thwomp! I know you're there!
Well, the game gave it to me, so I'm going to use it!
And... All that did was bring me back here...
I hope door four is not a bore...
Red and green P-switches?
D'oh! I missed... Well, at least I can reach the side exit this time.
Okay, good. I'm done with that area, which also means I'm done with the first four doors!
Is there another teleport block somewhere that I missed?
Find out next time! To be continued...
Aha! I thought there might be another trap there! Maybe I should scroll the screen to set those off early.
Wait, what just happened there? Let's take a look at the slow-motion instant replay...
So, what awaits me through the red door?
MOOOONN!!! Wait, it's red, so... Yeah, it's a fake...
Not to mention the fact that you don't even need all of the Aqua Switches to reach that cape! Was that block placed there intentionally? Sure doesn't seem like an accident...
Hello, and welcome back to EVW! It's finally time to take on the Source of Variety! I've already stocked up on mushrooms at Yoshi's House, so let's do this thing!
Well, I remain seriously stumped for a while, so I'm going to fast-forward a chunk of this footage...
Wow, it's like every spike in the book was used to construct this place!
BARF!

This is... This is crazy! Do you know how badly this breaks the game?! With side exit enabled, you can easily take these capes out of this level and use them in any other levels that haven't been cleared yet!
Let's try exploring to the right this time...
Red turn blocks are fake, obviously.
Take FIVE!!!
Now, supposedly, I needed the four aqua switches hit, so I'm guessing there's going to be something like a switch block bridge at the start...
Oh, right. The red ground is harmful, but I take it that green-stemmed muncher is safe?
Another ledge with a mushroom and a red door... Must be for later in the level. And if I keep going further right?
I probably should've duck-jumped onto the vines there.
And, let me guess... The side exit is active, right?
I guess some parts of this bridge are Mario only-- The moving spikes can pass through, but Mario can't. (Fortunately, there doesn't seem to be a hidden hole that I can fall through!)
BARF!
And, let me guess... I can go "out of bounds" here.
I guess not...
These upside-down purple blocks are acting like conveyor belts... So I guess each block has different properties.
And now we've got these things, but they shouldn't be hard to dodge...
Ow! Well, hello there, Mr. Surprise Thwomp! How's it going?
Uhh... I have some questions about this place...
BARF! Can I stop screwing up for a moment please?!
Ow! What the heck?
I think this teleport block is a little glitchy. I had to duck-jump into it to make it work.
Oh, now it's getting tricky! If I just focus on the munchers' colors and not worry about the coins, I should be fine.
Oh, it puts me here! But, thanks to the power of flight, I can easily go back and try the other doors!
It doesn't seem like I can open these blocks...
Whoa! That one is like a koopa shell! I wonder if I'll need it later...
Also, I don't see any Police or Fire stations, and I'm sure the residents will be demanding a Stadium soon...
Yeah, my time's running out, but I do find the solution soon...
I wonder if this is Bowser's training ground for when somebody decides to play around with the "Disasters" option in the actual SimCity...
Oh, you can climb on these! (I don't know what made me think to try that...)
Fortunately, because of the side exit, if I fall, I can try to hit the side of the screen to avoid losing a life. I still have to restart the level, though, but it's not like I got very far...
But what happens if I fly to the right when the screen scrolling doesn't stop?
BARF! Clean up in aisle two!
And now where am I?
Okay... Skip the mushroom since I have capes... Hmm... It looks like I've got some doors to choose from here.
Round 4. FIGHT!
Second attempt. Actually, these aren't quite as bad as the Mega Man blocks, because I can still see their positions when they're in "I can't stand on them" mode.
Okay, here we go, for real this time! Wait... I can hit that one block there, but it's probably just a mushroom if anything. There's no way that it could possibly be a cape, right?
You know... they should build train tracks instead of roads here. It'll cut down on the pollution.
Oh, I see. The red coins subtract from my coin counter. That's interesting...
I hate custom block glitches...
Oh, those black ones hurt you. Do tell...
Oh, and that's a bottomless pit...
Red koopa, green spiny... I wonder who's actually who? (Of course, if I spin jump, I'm safe either way!)
Gee, I wonder where the exit is...
First door...
And I can swim in this green lava-- Oh! I get it. Green=good and red=bad. It makes perfect sense!
Those blue ones are water tiles...
Well, I'd like to explore the third door right now, but my time limit is low, so I'm going to leave the level for a moment to reset the clock (and get another feather).
Uh, huh. Well, I'm not going to fool around out here.
I probably don't want to touch those vines. Also, what does this P-switch do?
Well said, Ralph and Cary. Okay, this time can I maybe please go two minutes without self-destructing myself!?
Those are some neat looking spikes...
Seriously?! The game is just handing me a cape at the beginning of Source of Variety?! And I can get another one easily by cape spinning the block on the right!
Yep, there's the solution. However, what was the point of the "shells" and that other room then? Were they just to trick me? Probably.
Oh, boy. Better hurry!
It acts like a gray P-switch, but I can't get the coins for some reason...
Okay, so we have red and green coins... (It's a little too early for Christmas...)
Okay, third door... Hopefully this'll go better than the second door did...
Ah, I finally hit the edge, then end up leaving the level due to the side exit. Okay, let's go back in and start exploring some doors!
Third attempt. In order to avoid clipping through the edge of the blocks like that, I should try aiming for the center of them.
Second door...
Nuts!
Pay attention. One of the black blocks above is actually a teleport block.
And that white one is a teleport block.
It's boss time... Or, maybe SimCity time? These commercial zones are toggling on and off sort of like certain infamous Mega Man blocks...
Yep. Makes sense, although this might become an unintended means of leaving the level later on...
